    <title>How I forced VSCode Remote+Codex to work inside Ubuntu-in-Termux on Android</title>
    <link href="https://blog.junyu33.me/en/2026/03/28/termux/"/>
    <id>https://blog.junyu33.me/en/2026/03/28/termux/</id>
    <updated>2026-03-27T20:30:00.000Z</updated>
    <summary type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Ever since I rapidly got into vibe coding last December, I wanted to try installing the Codex extension on every machine that could run VSCode. So my next target was that abandoned Android phone. In theory, Android (before Google <a href="https://keepandroidopen.org">hadn't yet done all the bad things it could</a>) can install Termux, and the latter even has a <a href="https://github.com/MFDGaming/ubuntu-in-termux">script</a> to nest Ubuntu inside it. So in theory, installing Remote SSH and Codex on that Android phone should be possible. But in practice...</p>]]></summary>
