    <title>Why does elliptic curve point addition satisfy the associative law?</title>
    <link href="https://blog.junyu33.me/en/2025/08/10/cayley/"/>
    <id>https://blog.junyu33.me/en/2025/08/10/cayley/</id>
    <updated>2025-08-10T03:30:00.000Z</updated>
    <summary type="html"><![CDATA[<p>This article introduces the proof of the associativity law for elliptic curve point addition, as well as the stronger 9-point theorem. Additionally, it covers three corollaries of this theorem: Pascal's theorem, Pappus' theorem, and the polar principle of pole and polar for conic sections.</p>]]></summary>
